This also changes how you think about money.

Don’t ask:

“Can we afford the dream?”

Ask:

“What is the cheapest experiment that meaningfully reduces uncertainty?”

Examples:

Instead of spending $25,000 on a custom tube…

Spend $500 wrapping a stock tube.

Then ask:

Did people actually prefer it?

If yes…

Now you’ve earned the right to invest.

If no…

You just saved yourself $25,000.

