One thing I’d add to the playbook

The Wild Hawg Upgrade Ledger

Every idea goes into one of four buckets.

Must Have (Launch)

Without these, don’t launch.

* Great taste
* Safe and compliant formula
* Reliable manufacturer
* Professional branding
* Functional packaging

⸻

Should Have (Early Growth)

* Subscription option
* More flavors
* Better packaging finish
* Strong influencer content

⸻

Could Have (Scale)

* Custom molded container
* Embossed logo
* Collector editions
* Seasonal releases

⸻

Someday (Dream)

These are intentionally parked.

Examples:

* Smart packaging
* Limited artist collaborations
* Custom dispenser
* Licensing deals
* Apparel line
* Hunting gear accessories

Nothing is thrown away.

It just waits until the business can support it.

⸻

The mindset I’d keep

You’ve already hinted at it:

Build a business that funds its own evolution.

That’s how many durable consumer brands have grown. The first version isn’t the final vision—it’s the engine that finances the next version. If Wild Hawg develops a loyal customer base early, those customers become the funding source for better flavors, better packaging, and more ambitious products instead of requiring you to bet everything upfront. That’s a much more resilient way to build a brand.